  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of this study is to evaluate the safety and efficacy of ID1201 in patients with
      mild Alzheimer's disease
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      ID1201 is a fruit extract of Melia toosendan. ID1201 alleviates Alzheimer's disease-type
      pathologies and cognitive deficit through the various actions of its effective components
      such as α-secretase activation followed to Aβ reduction, RAGE inhibition, neuro-protection,
      and anti-inflammatory activities.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
